<h3>League Rules for 2019:</h3>
<ol>
    <li>Games will be double header, 7 inning games: first game will be at 6:30 pm; second game approximately at 7:30 pm.  <strong>In the event that the score is tied at 7:30, game 1 continues into additional innings until a winner is determined.  Each inning will start with 1 out and the previous inning's last out on second base.</strong>  At the start of the evening, coaches should confer and determine which team will be home for each of the games.</li>
    <li>Each team brings one good and one reserve ball.</li>
    <li>Players must abide by the restrictions of the church they play for and also follow the rules of the field they are playing on, such as no smoking or chewing tobacco, no alcoholic beverages and <strong>NO FOUL LANGUAGE.  FIRST OFFENSE WARNING, SECOND OFFENSE SAME GAME KICKED OUT (Opposite Coach's Discretion)</strong></li>
    <li>Each team shall supply one umpire.</li>
    <li>Coaches and umpires will go over ground rules prior to the start of first game.  Two head coaches should decide any disputes.  Respect the ground rules for each field.</li>
    <li>No metal spikes.</li>
    <li>Date of game may be changed if two teams mutually agree.  Rainouts will be done on the same basis.</li>
    <li>Eight run rule per inning unless behind.   Even in last inning.</li>
    <li>If a game is rained out after the 5<sup>th</sup> inning, high score wins.  Tornado watch in effect at 5:30 pm cancels the game.  Use discretion.</li>
    <li>In field fly rule is in effect with men on 1<sup>st</sup> and 2<sup>nd</sup> bases, or loaded, and less than two outs.</li>
    <li>The arc of the pitch must be over the pitcher and batter's head, whoever is tallest.  Flat pitch is considered a ball.  Unlimited arc height.  All must be called in air.</li>
    <li>Batter goes to the plate with one ball/one strike count.</li>
    <li>Batter must start in batter box.</li>
    <li>No leading off bases.   No leaving the base until <u>contact</u> with the bat or the plate.  (One warning then out.)</li>
    <li><strong>One sub runner per inning.  (Coaches may agree on more if discussed and agreed prior to the start of the game.)</strong></li>
    <li>Catcher must be aware of what is going on by standing in front of the plate.</li>
    <li>The plate plus carpet is all considered the strike zone.  The ball must strike the plate/carpet to be called a strike.  The total zone is carpet + plate = 3'.</li>
    <li>2<sup>nd</sup> foul after the 2<sup>nd</sup> strike is an out.</li>
    <li>15 fun rule after the 5<sup>th</sup> inning is in effect during tournament only.</li>
    <li>A player must play in at least six <u>regular</u> season games to be eligible for tournament play.</li>
    <li>If the commissioner is made aware of a ringer, they will check your book.</li>
    <li>Caught foul tip above the catcher's head before the 2<sup>nd</sup> strike is an out.  After the 2<sup>nd</sup> strike, caught foul tip is out.</li>
    <li>The umpire can call a TIME OUT when the ball is in the PITCHER'S hand without it being requested.   Time out by the umpire should be called only when requested by the fielder or runner and by his own discretion that play has stopped.</li>
    <li>A fair ball hit to the outfield that rolls past the in play boundary of the field shall be an automatic double, whether it is touched or not.</li>
    <li>All bats must have an ASA certified stamp on them.</li>
    <li>Any player who knowningly or unknowingly uses an illegal bat will be called out.</li>
    <li>If the bat is used after being noticed the game wil be forfeited.   Safety is more important.</li>
    <li>Home runs are limited to 8 per team, per game.  <strong>After 8, each home run is an out.</strong>  Does not apply to inside the park home runs.  Runners only advance if bases are loaded.</li>
    <li>To speed up the game, Homeruns will be run to first only.</li>
    <li><strong>Batters may not have a pinch runner out of the box unless both teams agree prior to the start of the game.  If both teams do not agree, then the batter has to make it to first.</li>
</ol>
